  "markup": "\u003Cp\u003ETreating Senior Citizens can offer a bit of a challenge in some cases, but these challenges can be easily met with the right treatment protocols.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EPeople are living longer and are much more active later in life than ever before.\u0026nbsp; More than 10,000 baby boomers a day will turn 65, a pattern that will continue for the next 19 years.\u0026nbsp; That is 69,350,000 people with all the aches and pains that come with aging and in most cases can benefit from Super Pulsed Laser.\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EWe will discuss various common conditions for Boomers and beyond, and how to address them with Super Pulsed Laser, such as degenerating knee and persistent back pain.\u003C/p\u003E\nJoin Chris Carraway DC, and Terrance Baker MD, for an in-depth look at this challenging population segment."
}]]></Value>
